esponse","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The real failure boundary is: does the code send the right data shape and parse the real API response correctly? A mock at the Unit level might verify call args, but would miss issues with actual API response format, status codes, or parsing edge cases. Integration-level mock (mock HTTP layer with realistic response fixtures) catches both the send and parse sides.","test_description":"Mock HTTP POST to payer endpoint. Verify request body includes patient_id and plan_code in correct JSON structure. Provide three response fixtures: {eligible: true}, {eligible: false}, {eligible: null}. Verify code correctly parses each, extracts status, and does not crash on edge cases (e.g., missing optional fields).","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.85,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When payer API is unreachable, system marks eligibility as 'pending' and continues intake rather than blocking","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The behavior requires testing both: (1) eligibility check returns 'pending' on API error, AND (2) downstream steps (triage, scheduling) are invoked despite the error. Testing only the eligibility function in Unit would miss whether the orchestration continues. Integration test with mocked API error + mocked downstream modules verifies the full flow.","test_description":"Mock payer HTTP to raise TimeoutError. Mock downstream triage, scheduling, confirmation steps to track if they're called. Verify eligibility returns status 'pending'. Verify triage() and schedule() are invoked despite API error. Confirm intake completes without throwing exception and does not block on failure.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"AI symptom triage correctly assigns high urgency to symptom combinations that indicate emergency conditions (e.g., chest pain + shortness of breath)","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The real failure is: the real AI/ML medical reasoning model does not classify chest_pain+SOB as high urgency. A mock will always pass, hiding the actual classification failure. Correctness depends on what the real model produces, not on code logic. Must call the real model to verify it produces the right urgency level.","test_description":"Call real medical reasoning engine with symptoms {chest_pain: true, shortness_of_breath: true}. Verify returned urgency_level is 'high' or numeric equivalent ≥ threshold. Test additional emergency combinations (severe_anaphylaxis, stroke_symptoms, severe_trauma). Verify all return high urgency. Run multiple times if model is non-deterministic to build confidence.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.9,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Symptom triage produces natural language explanation of urgency assessment that clinician can review, not just numeric score","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The real failure is: the real AI model returns only a numeric score with no explanation text. A mock returning fake explanation text will hide this. Correctness depends on whether the real model produces explanation; must call real model to verify both urgency AND explanation fields are present and coherent.","test_description":"Submit symptoms to real AI triage engine. Verify response includes both urgency_level field AND explanation_text field (non-empty). Verify explanation contains medical reasoning (e.g., references to symptoms, risk factors, clinical context), not just generic text. Assert response structure includes explanation and is not {urgency: 'high'} alone.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0,"Agentic":0.9,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Appointment scheduled in first available s